  "title": "Course Facilitator/STEM Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>Innoreal is an education company that engages in grade 1-12 education and career guidance services. It advocates AI literacy and entrepreneurship from childhood and focuses on skill development in both fields. It also supports students with tutoring and college applications.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will empower students to develop practical skills in Python, Data Science, and Machine Learning by guiding them through building models and debugging code. You will also deliver engaging, hands-on activities in Scratch AI, Robotics (Viam/LEGO), and Generative Art to make AI concepts tangible and enjoyable.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Guide students to build and debug Python-based data science and machine learning models, enhancing their coding proficiency and problem-solving skills</li><li>Design and facilitate tactile, unplugged activities using Scratch AI, Robotics (Viam/LEGO), and Generative Art to teach AI logic in an interactive and accessible manner</li><li>Foster student engagement by creating learning experiences that translate complex AI concepts into physical, fun exercises</li><li>Support students’ understanding of computer science fundamentals through practical, outcome-driven instruction</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Background in computer science as a teacher, major, or related job field<br />International school Teacher <br />Fun Creative Know enquire based learning</li></ul>",
